CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 23, 1960, pg. 2, reads: " 'Luxurious Rentals, Non-luxurious Apartments - There are many who believe that there is no place like home, but some tenants, one in particular, in 'luxury apartments' at 71 [711] Wandless St., Hill District, are not so sure. The rentals are too high for the poor living conditions of the apartments, they charge...  Upper right, while the resident of this apartment was away on her vacation, a sheriff's sale sign was posted on her 'home.'  The landlord said she was two weeks late in paying her rent.  Residents said that although the landlord had entered other apartments before, he never had posted a sheriff's sale sign on any of them... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Sheriff's Sale sign hung on door of apartment in building on 711 Wandless Street, Hill District
